Section 5                    Baked Apples 
                         by Andrea Lemieux, RNCP 

 Read about Andrea Lemieux on our Meet the Team 
             page; http://www.Life-Choices.com/team.html 

Serves 4. 
4 large apples 
1 cup raisins, plumped in hot water for 3 minutes, then drained, 
- or - chopped dates 
1 orange, grated rind and juiced (be sure it is organic when using 
the peel) 
1/4 teaspoon cinnamon 
1/4 teaspoon ground ginger 
1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract (optional) 
pinch of Celtic sea salt 

1. Preheat oven to 350#186#F. 
2. Core the apples and peel a 1-inch strip around center of 
apple or pierce skin with a fork to prevent bursting. Place 
apples in baking dish. 
3. Mix remaining ingredients, except orange juice, in a bowl. 
Fill center of each apple. 
4. Pour orange juice into baking dish around apples. 
5. Bake uncovered at 350#186#F for 40 minutes or until soft when 
tested with a fork. 

