                Curried Sweet Potato and Apple Soup 

With the end of August upon us, we can begin to think about 
warming soups, using the produce of the season. This soup 
combines apple and sweet potato. You can substitute the 
sweet potato with winter squash, or use half squash and half 
sweet potato. Kobacha squash is particularly good as it is 
dense and sweet. 

Serves 5 - 6 

2 tablespoons extra virgin olive oil or ghee 
3 leeks, white part only, well washed and chopped 
1 medium onion, chopped 
2 medium carrots, chopped 
2 large cloves garlic, chopped 
1 teaspoon grated fresh ginger root 
4#189# cups vegetable or chicken broth (homemade, salt free) 
1#189# pounds sweet potatoes, peeled and cut into 1i cubes 
1 medium Granny Smith apple, cored, peeled and cubed 
1 teaspoon curry powder 
Celtic sea salt and pepper to taste 

1. Heat the oil or ghee over medium heat in a soup pot. Add 
onion, garlic, ginger root and leeks, sautee about 5 minutes, 
until onions are transluscent. 
2. Add remaining ingredients, stir. 
3. Cover, bring to a light boil, reduce heat to low. Cook until 
potatoes are tender, about 1 hour. 
4. Puree in batches in food processor, return to pot and heat 
through before serving. 

